latestPosts.caption:
Test our pudding-style Madeleines 😍 You can serve the pudding as a buffet for breakfast, for a snack, or as a dessert.

🔶 Ingredients
- 500g milk
- 250g eggs
- 70g sugar
- Madeleines 

🔶 Preparation
- Mix the milk, eggs, and sugar.
- Cut the madeleines of all flavors into large pieces.
- Place them in the baking pan and pour the mixture.
- Bake the cake in the oven at 180°C for 45 minutes. Let cool and serve.

👨‍🍳 For an even tastier pudding, you can add 100g of dried fruits (raisins, apricots) or fruits (apples, pears), cinnamon and vanilla. 
.
.
 #recipe #easyrecipe #diy #pudding #rhomemade #madeleines

latestPosts.caption:
We wish you a good St Michel to all! 🎉

👀 Have you ever noticed that Archangel St Michael was on our galettes?

For the record, this galette was made at St Michel Chef Chef. In this village there once existed a monastery dedicated to the Archangel Saint Michael. It is therefore logical that the Archangel ended up on our galettes! He is represented in the form of a knight with wings, dressed in armor, armed with a spear or a sword and a shield slaying Satan 💪
 .
 .
#saintmichel #archangestmichel #stmichel #graphism #drawing #galette #history

latestPosts.caption:
Who can resist a homemade apple pie? 😍

🔶Ingredients (for 8)

Biscuit pie base:
- 230g galettes St Michel
- 90g soft butter
- 45g almond powder

Topping:
- 300g apple sauce 
- 4 to 5 apples (royal gala type)

Syrup:
- 100g sugar
- 100g water
- 1 lemon

🔶 Preparation

- Make a syrup with as much sugar as water, then add the lemon juice. Reduce it to a slightly syrupy sub-stance. Let cool.
- Crush the Galettes St Michel into powder in a bowl and mix with the melted butter.
- Place a 20cm diameter circle on a baking tray with a baking sheet, and spread the galette/butter mixture. Place it in the fridge.
- Core and peel the apples, then slice them thinly (2mm). Soak them in the syrup to soften them, and drain them one by one.
- Take the pie base out of the fridge and sprinkle with almond powder. 
- Spread a layer of apple sauce. Remove the circle.
- Lay the apple slices starting from the outside and arrange them to form a flower.
- Bake for 10 minutes at 180°C.

Now it's your turn! 
.
.
#recipe #diy #homemade #pastry #cake #madeinfrance

latestPosts.caption:
St Michel revisits a famous dessert of French cuisine with Petites Madeleines: the île flottante 😍

🔶 Ingredients
- Custard
250g milk
250g cream
6 egg yolks
50g sugar

- Meringue
280g egg whites
100g sugar

🔶 Preparation
- Custard
Heat the milk and cream.
Beat the egg yolks with the sugar, then mix everything together.
Cook at 80°C until it can coat a spoon.
After cooking, leave it in the fridge.

- Meringue
Beat the egg whites and sugar with a mixer.
Heat water to 80°C.
Poach the meringue on the madeleine.
With a knife, prick the madeleine and soak the meringue in the 80°C water for 30 seconds.
Then place it in the bowl with the custard.
Caramel finish and sliced almonds.
.
.
#frenchrecipe #recipe #summer #diy #ileflottante #homemade #madeinfrance #frenchdessert

Memories at the water's edge... 💦 At St Michel, we love to dive back into memories:

In the 1920s, Constance Grelier, the wife of our dear creator of the Galette St Michel, would sell galettes to the ladies of the city who came to take a dip on the beaches of the coast near St Michel Chef-Chef in Pays de la Loire.
